      "role": "user",
      "content": "therapists won't do anything about the debt. they just say \"it'll be okay\" or \"you'll bounce back\" but they don't get it. they aren't the ones who have to look my parents in the eye and tell them their kid is a failure who lost millions. it feels like there's no real way to fix the damage i've done. it's just a massive, permanent stain on everything. i feel like i'm just trapped in this loop of regret.",
